---
description:
Defines the reusable component architecture for LexMastery. Every screen must be composed from reusable components instead of ad-hoc widgets.

alwaysApply: true
---

# Component Library

LexMastery uses a centralized design system.

Every UI element should come from the component library before creating a new widget.

Never duplicate UI.

---

# Design Philosophy

Components should be:

Reusable

Composable

Accessible

Theme-aware

Responsive

Stateless whenever possible

---

# Component Hierarchy

Design Tokens

↓

Primitive Components

↓

Composite Components

↓

Feature Components

↓

Screens

Never skip layers.

---

# Folder Structure

lib/

shared/

components/

buttons/

inputs/

cards/

dialogs/

navigation/

feedback/

layouts/

surfaces/

icons/

Feature-specific widgets belong inside the feature.

---

# Primitive Components

Examples

LMButton

LMText

LMIcon

LMAvatar

LMBadge

LMDivider

LMSpacer

These should never contain business logic.

---

# Composite Components

Examples

Lesson Card

Course Card

Quiz Card

AI Message Bubble

Progress Card

Score Card

Continue Learning Card

---

# Screen Components

Screens compose components.

They do not implement them.

---

# Naming Convention

Prefix every reusable component.

Example

LMButton

LMCard

LMSearchField

LMProgressIndicator

Avoid generic names.

---

# Component API

Components should expose only meaningful properties.

Avoid exposing internal implementation details.

---

# Styling

Never hardcode:

colors

typography

spacing

radius

elevation

Everything comes from tokens.

---

# State

Reusable components should remain stateless whenever possible.

Interactive behavior belongs in controllers.

---

# Variants

Components support variants.

Example

Primary

Secondary

Outlined

Ghost

Danger

Never create duplicate widgets.

---

# Accessibility

Every component must expose:

Semantic labels

Touch target ≥48dp

Keyboard focus

Screen reader support

---

# Documentation

Every reusable component should include:

Purpose

Usage

Properties

Examples

Accessibility notes

---

# Cursor Instructions

Before generating a widget:

Search for an existing reusable component.

Reuse before creating new.